<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com/2019-in-review-calendar-makeovers-new-plugins-and-upgraded-features/">2019 in Review: Calendar Makeovers, New Plugins and Upgraded Features</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>
";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"Lauren";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11256:"<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Weâ€™re feeling a little sentimental, and itâ€™s not just because of the holidays. Here at The Events Calendar, weâ€™re reflecting back on 10 years of being a part of the WordPress community. Thatâ€™s a lot of years, with lots of great memories and highlights.Â </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Over the past decade, weâ€™ve introduced more than 10 different plugins and add-ons that power WordPress calendars and make it easy for you to manage your events, every step of the way. Weâ€™re proud to play a role in powering our usersâ€™ events and, ultimately, in bringing people together for events around the world.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Weâ€™re also proud of what weâ€™ve accomplished in 2019. In this year alone, we&#8217;ve helped our customers with </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">25,000 </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">support tickets and sent out </span>58<span style="font-weight: 400;"> updates and releases for our plugins.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">But we havenâ€™t just worked hard on the day-to-day maintenance of The Events Calendar. Weâ€™ve also dedicated lots of time and energy this year to releasing </span><a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/product/promoter/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">a brand-new product</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and completing the first-ever makeover of The Events Calendarâ€”and thatâ€™s just the tip of the iceberg. Hereâ€™s a look back at some of our biggest projects and accomplishments in 2019:</span></p>
<h2><b>We announced the first-ever redesign of The Events Calendar.</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The biggest news of 2019: We announced </span><a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/first-look-the-events-calendar-redesign/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the first major redesign of The Events Calendar</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. This sleek new look officially drops in 2020 (commence the countdown!), but some users have joined our beta launch so they can be the first to test drive the new calendar views.</span><a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/first-look-the-events-calendar-redesign/"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1889372 size-large" src="https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/10/views-redesign-mobile-views-665x326.png" alt="New mobile views for Month view and List view." width="665" height="326" srcset="https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/10/views-redesign-mobile-views-665x326.png 665w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/10/views-redesign-mobile-views-140x69.png 140w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/10/views-redesign-mobile-views-300x147.png 300w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/10/views-redesign-mobile-views-768x377.png 768w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/10/views-redesign-mobile-views-430x211.png 430w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/10/views-redesign-mobile-views-645x316.png 645w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/10/views-redesign-mobile-views-1068x524.png 1068w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/10/views-redesign-mobile-views-460x226.png 460w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/10/views-redesign-mobile-views-600x294.png 600w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/10/views-redesign-mobile-views-500x245.png 500w" sizes="(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px" /></a></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The makeover includes a new, elevated aesthetic thatâ€™s design-forward, but still flexible enough to blend in with any website. Plus, we made improvements to mobile views, added a new style for featured events, and addressed a number of known user pain points. Keep your eyes peeled in January for news about the official launch. In the meantime, </span><a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/behind-the-scenes-building-the-events-calendars-new-look/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">you can read up on what went into creating the new look behind the scenes.</span></a></p>
<h2><b>We introduced Promoter to make email marketing for events easier than ever.</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Exporting attendee lists from WordPress and managing them through a separate email application used to be cumbersome and time-consuming. No more!Â </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">In 2019, we were excited to launch </span><b><a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/product/promoter/">Promoter</a>,</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> an add-on that works with The Events Calendar and Event Tickets (or Event Tickets Plus) to manage all of your contacts from within your WordPress dashboard with no extra steps.</span></p>
<p><a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/product/promoter/"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1723435 size-large" src="https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/02/blog-post-665x333.jpg" alt="" width="665" height="333" srcset="https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/02/blog-post-665x333.jpg 665w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/02/blog-post-140x70.jpg 140w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/02/blog-post-300x150.jpg 300w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/02/blog-post-768x384.jpg 768w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/02/blog-post-430x215.jpg 430w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/02/blog-post-645x323.jpg 645w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/02/blog-post-1068x534.jpg 1068w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/02/blog-post-460x230.jpg 460w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/02/blog-post-600x300.jpg 600w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/02/blog-post-500x250.jpg 500w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/02/blog-post.jpg 1256w" sizes="(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px" /></a></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Promoter has quickly become a beloved member of The Events Calendar family by helping users streamline their email process and schedule messages in a snap with shortcuts.</span></p>
<h2><b>Split payments changed the game for community calendars.</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This fall, we rolled out </span><a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/split-payments-a-game-changer-for-ticket-sales/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">split payments</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to Community Tickets users. This feature makes it easy for calendar owners to earn revenue on tickets that are sold by event organizers, and payments are split right at the time of purchase: Calendar owners receive a fee or portion of each ticket sale, and the rest of the ticket earnings will go directly to the event organizer.Â </span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone wp-image-1853370 size-large" src="https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/08/split-payments-665x333.png" alt="" width="665" height="333" srcset="https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/08/split-payments-665x333.png 665w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/08/split-payments-140x70.png 140w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/08/split-payments-300x150.png 300w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/08/split-payments-768x384.png 768w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/08/split-payments-430x215.png 430w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/08/split-payments-645x323.png 645w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/08/split-payments-1068x534.png 1068w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/08/split-payments-460x230.png 460w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/08/split-payments-600x300.png 600w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/08/split-payments-500x250.png 500w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/08/split-payments.png 1256w" sizes="(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">That means you (the calendar owner) get your cut and pay out event organizers in one fell swoop: No need to divvy up the earnings after the sales period ends. Less busy work + more $ in your pocket? Sounds like a win to us!</span></p>
<h2><b>A new attendee registration modal for Event Tickets Plus brought major upgrades to ticket sales.</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Back in 2018, we laid the groundwork for improvements to the attendee registration experience in Event Tickets Plus. The goal: Make it easier for you to collect attendee registration information.Â </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Then in 2019, we took things a step further by releasing a brand-new </span><a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/ticket-registration-just-got-a-whole-lot-better/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">attendee registration modal</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> that pops up when a user selects tickets to purchase.</span><img class="alignnone wp-image-1942846 size-large" src="https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/12/Ticket-Registration-665x333.png" alt="" width="665" height="333" srcset="https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/12/Ticket-Registration-665x333.png 665w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/12/Ticket-Registration-140x70.png 140w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/12/Ticket-Registration-300x150.png 300w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/12/Ticket-Registration-768x384.png 768w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/12/Ticket-Registration-430x215.png 430w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/12/Ticket-Registration-645x323.png 645w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/12/Ticket-Registration-1068x534.png 1068w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/12/Ticket-Registration-460x230.png 460w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/12/Ticket-Registration-600x300.png 600w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/12/Ticket-Registration-500x250.png 500w, https://s3.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2019/12/Ticket-Registration.png 1256w" sizes="(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This is a big deal for two reasons: It keeps attendees on the same webpage and eliminates lag time moving between screens. It also adds flexibility for users to update their purchase right within the modal. They can add and remove tickets and update ticket details without ever leaving the pop-up modal. Users can even save the tickets in their cart and go back to shopping without losing any registration details.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">To sweeten the deal, we also updated the checkout design and incorporated intelligent checkout features that prompt users to update ticket details before purchasing. The result is a serious upgrade to the user experience for your attendees. Happy attendees = happy calendar owners = happy us. (We just like to see everyone happy.)</span></p>
<p>Thanks for coming along for the ride this year, and we can&#8217;t wait for all that 2020 brings!</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com/2019-in-review-calendar-makeovers-new-plugins-and-upgraded-features/">2019 in Review: Calendar Makeovers, New Plugins and Upgraded Features</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>
