";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Courtney";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3835:"<p>Hey folks! Today&#8217;s update fixes errors mostly on larger sites caused by extra queries running on pages. Also, Event Tickets would only update properly if Event Tickets Plus was updated first. We&#8217;ve reversed that and updates will run properly again.</p>
<p>In most cases, you will be able to take advantage of automated updates directly in WordPress, but if thatâ€™s unavailable for some reason, you can <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/my-account/downloads/">download the plugins</a> from the downloads page in your account, then <a href="https://support.theeventscalendar.com/260486-Manual-Updates">update manually</a>.</p>
<p>The changes are short and simple this time:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="#et">Event Tickets 4.11.0.1</a></li>
<li><a href="#etp">Event Tickets Plus 4.11.0.1</a></li>
<li><a href="#not-updated">Not Updated This Release</a></li>
</ul>
<hr />
<p><!-- https://github.com/moderntribe/event-tickets/blob/release/ar-modal/readme.txt --></p>
<h3 id="et">Event Tickets 4.11.0.1</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Users reported high CPU usage causing sites to not respond. We now avoid running extra queries when registering assets.</li>
<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Event Tickets would only update properly if Event Tickets Plus was updated first. That was backwards. We protected <samp>Tribe__Tickets__Tickets::get_tickets()</samp> to avoid errors with it not being public before upgrading Event Tickets Plus. Updates run properly again.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<p><!-- https://github.com/moderntribe/event-tickets-plus/blob/044b03857b4ac077f15f09f30a185b7dac3bff50/readme.txt#L136 --></p>
<h3 id="etp">Event Tickets Plus 4.11.0.1</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Our admin notice describing the <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/event-tickets-4-11-redesigning-tickets-and-attendee-registration/">Attendee Registration feature</a> was creating performance issues. To clean that up, we are preventing Composer Autoloader from taking too much time loading files and have stopped autoloading a class unnecessarily on each page load.</li>
<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Fatal errors are never desirable. We&#8217;ve corrected a bad <samp>self</samp> reference in <samp>Tribe__Tickets_Plus__Commerce__WooCommerce__Meta</samp>.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3 id="not-updated">Not Updated This Release</h3>
<p>The following plugins have <em>not</em> been updated this release and will remain at the version numbers specified here:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-events-calendar/">The Events Calendar</a>Â  4.9.13</li>
<li><a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-events-calendar-pro/">Events Calendar Pro</a>Â 4.7.10</li>
<li><a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-events-filterbar/">Filter Bar</a> 4.8.1</li>
<li><a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-community-events/">Community Events</a>Â 4.6.1.1</li>
<li><a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/product/community-tickets/">Community Tickets</a>Â 4.7.0</li>
<li><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/advanced-post-manager/">Advanced Post Manager</a> 4.5</li>
<li><a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-eventbrite-tickets/">Eventbrite Tickets</a> 4.6.3</li>
<li><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/image-widget/">Image Widget</a> 4.4.7</li>
<li><a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-image-widget-plus/">Image Widget Plus</a> 1.0.3</li>
<li><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/GigPress">GigPress</a> 2.3.23</li>
</ul>
