<p><!-- https://github.com/moderntribe/the-events-calendar/blob/release/B19.15/Â  --></p>
<h3 id="tec">The Events Calendar 4.9.12</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; We resolved an issue that prevented the Block Editor from saving the date and time of an event correctly in WordPress 5.3.</li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; We have added the <samp>tribe_get_query_var</samp> function, which fixed an error where the <a href="https://support.theeventscalendar.com/074168-Embedding-Calendar-Views-with-the-tribe_events-Shortcode">[tribe_events]</a> shortcode was freezing up.</li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; We have added <samp>tribe_get_the_content()</samp> and <samp>tribe_the_content()</samp> to improve PHP 7.2 compatibility with WordPress 5.2.</li>
<li><strong>Hooks</strong> &#8211; <a href="https://docs.theeventscalendar.com/reference/since/tribe.common4.9.21/">https://docs.theeventscalendar.com/reference/since/tribe.common4.9.21/</a></li>
<li><strong>Language</strong> &#8211; <kbd>21 new strings added, 162 updated, 0 fuzzied, and 0 obsoleted</kbd></li>
</ul>
<hr />
<p><!-- https://github.com/moderntribe/events-pro/tree/release/B19.15Â  --></p>
<h3 id="pro">Events Calendar PRO 4.7.10</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; We are no longer using the <samp>date_default_timezone_set</samp> function after WordPress 5.3 discouraged its usage in any plugins or themes. This also happens to improve issues that some users have experienced with timezones.</li>
<li><strong>Language</strong> &#8211; <kbd>0 new strings added, 4 updated, 0 fuzzied, and 0 obsoleted</kbd></li>
</ul>
